# Log Messages Must Be Static — Use Tags for Dynamic Values

Log messages (the first argument to `logger.Info`, `logger.Warn`, `logger.Error`) must be **static strings** that describe what happened. All dynamic/variable values (run IDs, tasklist names, shard IDs, addresses, counts, etc.) must go in **tags**, not concatenated or interpolated into the message.

This makes log exploring, filtering, and aggregation dramatically easier in production.

## Exception

`logger.Debug` / `logger.DebugF` are exempt — debug logs are typically only enabled locally and readability there outweighs structure.

## Rules

- **No string concatenation** in log messages: never `"some event " + someVar`.
- **No fmt.Sprintf** for log messages: never `fmt.Sprintf("processed %s", id)`.
- The message should read like a template/event name: `"Run sync matched"`, `"Matcher stopped"`, `"Server listening"`.
- All context goes in tags: `tag.RunID(id)`, `tag.Namespace(ns)`, `tag.Address(addr)`, `tag.String("key", val)`, etc.

## Examples

```go
// BAD: dynamic values in message
m.logger.Info("Sync matched run " + req.RunId + " on tasklist " + tlName,
    tag.RunID(req.RunId))

// GOOD: static message, dynamic values in tags
m.logger.Info("Run sync matched",
    tag.RunID(req.RunId), tag.TaskListName(tlName))

// BAD: address in message
app.Logger.Info("Metrics HTTP server listening on " + listener.Addr().String())

// GOOD: address in tag
app.Logger.Info("Metrics HTTP server listening", tag.Address(listener.Addr().String()))

// BAD: concatenating identifiers
mgr.logger.Info("Tasklist claimed: " + namespace + "/" + taskListName)

// GOOD: each identifier in its own tag
mgr.logger.Info("Tasklist claimed", tag.Namespace(namespace), tag.TaskListName(taskListName))
```
